sec.p:
(1) Historical data set. In 1948, the British colonial government undertook exploratory fisheries surveys in different tropical archipelagos of the Indian Ocean including the Chagos archipelago (
  
   36
  ). Of 1281 hours of handlining carried out in different stations around the Chagos archipelago, the authors recorded 88% of gray reef sharks and 8% of silvertip sharks (that is, gray reef sharks on the order of seven sharks per hour of handlining and one silvertip shark every 40 min). We assumed that this catch composition was indicative of the species composition of the sampled shark community. Because we did not have information on the level of uncertainty around these percent values, we assumed an associated SE of 4%. We will call this approach the Wheeler scenario.
